  "raw_meta_yaml": "schema_version: 1\n\ncontext:\n  version: \"1.43.1\"\n\npackage:\n  name: buildah\n  version: ${{ version }}\n\nsource:\n  url: https://github.com/containers/buildah/archive/v${{ version }}.tar.gz\n  sha256: 7980a8b4fb719a104d592b06de149cc18766de02f8c3dd94e727f8702a62f9cd\n  # patches:\n    # NOTE: This adds the memfd_create syscall which is not available on CentOS 6's kernels.\n    # - 0001-Add-missing-defines-for-CentOS-6.patch\n    # - 0002-Use-config-files-in-prefix-as-fallback.patch\n\nbuild:\n  number: 0\n  skip: not linux\n  dynamic_linking:\n    binary_relocation: false\n  # Binary relocation causes:\n  #   buildah-in-a-user-namespace: error while loading shared libraries: libseccomp.so.2: cannot open shared object file: No such file or directory\n  # because of https://github.com/containers/buildah/commit/a6ed6883017fa8f1c7e6bd2ccd19e600107dd675\n\nrequirements:\n  build:\n    - ${{ compiler('c') }}\n    - ${{ stdlib('c') }}\n    - ${{ compiler('go-cgo') }}\n    - go-licenses\n    - make\n    - pkg-config\n  host:\n    - btrfs-progs\n    - containers-common\n    - gpgme\n    - libdevmapper\n    - libseccomp\n  run:\n    - conmon\n    - cni-plugins\n    - containers-common\n    - runc\n    - slirp4netns\n\ntests:\n  - script:\n      - buildah --help\n      - buildah --version\n\nabout:\n  license: Apache-2.0\n  license_file:\n    - LICENSE\n    - license-files/\n  summary: A command line tool that facilitates building OCI container images.\n  description: |\n    The Buildah package provides a command line tool which can be used to:\n\n    * Create a working container, either from scratch or using an image as a starting point.\n    * Mount a working container's root filesystem for manipulation.\n    * Unmount a working container's root filesystem.\n    * Use the updated contents of a container's root filesystem as a filesystem layer to create a new image.\n    * Delete a working container or an image.\n    * Rename a local container.\n\n\n  homepage: https://buildah.io\n  repository: https://github.com/containers/buildah\n  documentation: https://github.com/containers/buildah\n\nextra:\n  recipe-maintainers:\n    - dhirschfeld\n    - mbargull\n",
